mlpppIpNsTable.name: mlpppIpNsTable
mlpppIpNsTable.description: A table containing status parameters about each MLPPP module layer PPP IP Network Control Protocol.

mlpppIpNsEntry.name: mlpppIpNsEntry
mlpppIpNsEntry.description: Status parameters for a specific PPP IP Network Control Protocol.

mlpppIpNsLSapNumber.name: mlpppIpNsLSapNumber
mlpppIpNsLSapNumber.description: Indicates the row that contains objects for monitoring a SAP that is associated with one of the PPP links. Range of Values: 1-10 Default Value: none

mlpppIpNsNumber.name: mlpppIpNsNumber
mlpppIpNsNumber.description: Indicates the row that contains objects for monitoring a SAP that is associated with one of the PPP links. Range of Values: 1 Default Value: none

mlpppIpNsLocalToRemoteComp.name: mlpppIpNsLocalToRemoteComp
mlpppIpNsLocalToRemoteComp.description: Identifies whether the local end of the IP-PPP link is using TCP/IP header compression (vj-tcp) to send packets to the remote. The value of this object is determined when the PPP configuration is negotiated. The local port's preference for header compression is determined using mlpppIpNcComp of mlpppIpNcTable. Options: none (1) vj-tcp (2): header compression Default Value: None

mlpppIpNsRemoteToLocalComp.name: mlpppIpNsRemoteToLocalComp
mlpppIpNsRemoteToLocalComp.description: Identifies whether the remote end of the IP-PPP link is using TCP/IP header compression (vj-tcp) to send packets to the local end. The value of this object is determined when the PPP configuration is negotiated. The local port's preference for header compression is determined using mlpppIpNcComp of mlpppIpNcTable. Options: none (1) vj-tcp (2): header compression Default value: None

mlpppIpNcTable.name: mlpppIpNcTable
mlpppIpNcTable.description: A table containing configuration parameters about each MLPPP module layer's PPP IP Network Control Protocol.

mlpppIpNcEntry.name: mlpppIpNcEntry
mlpppIpNcEntry.description: The configuration parameters for a specific PPP IP Network Control Protocol.

mlpppIpNcUSapNumber.name: mlpppIpNcUSapNumber
mlpppIpNcUSapNumber.description: Indicates the row containing objects for monitoring a SAP that is associated with one of the MLPPP links . Range of Values: 1-10 Default Value: none

mlpppIpNcNumber.name: mlpppIpNcNumber
mlpppIpNcNumber.description: Indicates the row containing objects for monitoring a SAP associated with one of the MLPPP links. Range of Values: 1 Default Value: none

mlpppIpNcComp.name: mlpppIpNcComp
mlpppIpNcComp.reference: Section 4.0, Van Jacobson TCP/IP Header Compression of RFC1332.
mlpppIpNcComp.description: Determines whether the local end of PPP link wants to use TCP/IP header compression (vj-tcp) to send packets over the link. If header compression is desired, the local will negotiate for its implementation with the remote end of the link. The result of the negotiation is displayed in mlpppIpNsLocalToRemoteComp (the local) and mlpppIpNsRemoteToLocalComp (remote). If compression is not desired, there will be no attempt to negotiate with the other end of the link. Options: none (1) vj-tcp (2): header compression Default Value: none Configuration Changed: administrative
